article.headline: UCF 66, S. Dakota St. 64
article.story: CANCUN, Mexico -- Freshman guard Isaac Sosa scored a career-high 19 points, and Central Florida beat South Dakota State 66-64 on Saturday in the Cancun Challenge. Trailing by as many as 10 points in the second half, Central Florida (3-2) used a 10-2 run to get back in the game. the Knights led 65-64 with three seconds left when Garrett Callahan made two free throws, but Sosa missed one after getting fouled to seal it. Kai Williams scored 15 of his team-high 16 points in the first half for the Jackrabbits (2-4), who shot just 31.7 percent from the field.
